<br>
Depends. What're you looking for? I'm helping open up this great, new one called AtG. We're always looking for play-testers. Roleplaying enforced, not quite classic fantasy. Tons of great features, too. We're making completely different mobs from what's been out. I.e. instead of that lioness always aggroing on you, there's a 1% chance that it will, that 1% chance being something like you coming too close to the cubs, disturbing her territory, or so forth.<br>
<br>
There's a bunch of great roleplaying ones out there. Armageddon is a good one. Lotsa people like it. It takes place in a Dark Sun-like world. Decent roleplaying, but no ANSI color, and it takes a moment to go between rooms, which I don't like.<br>
<br>
If you're looking for PK, try something using a Godwars codebase. I played on some MUD before that started everyone off at the max level, level 50, and just set them against each other. That was A LOT of fun. Lost the address of that.<br>
<br>
It all depends on what you're looking for. MUSHs are for hardcore roleplaying, honestly. As in, all you do is roleplay, no levelling up or anything. They're fun, to a point. If no one's around, it gets really boring. And they're mostly for Tabletop games, such as Shadowrun or D&amp;D. Use mudconnector.com to search, though. Great site right there. If you need any more advice on MUDs, feel free to ask. <p>Vall Shadowstrife<BR>
Tier'Dal Scout of Luclin <BR>
Agent of The Ring <BR>
"I thought I saw my own worst enemy, a kind of demon. And it was me."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 12:51:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=292.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Close readings</span><hr size=1> Rexfelix (and others):<br>
<br>
A few times, you've said you directed your comments at Shintou's words.  But that's notwhat you actually said.  <br>
Let's take a closer look at what you initially posted:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What you [Shintou] are exhibiting is intolerance...which is a degree or two away from racism.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->In this quote, you say that Shintou is exhibiting intolerance, not that his words are intolerant.  There is a subtle, but important, difference--it's that same subtle difference that your claim (that you directed your comments at his words, not his character) depends on.  To &quot;exhibit&quot; is to &quot;display&quot;, to demonstrate, to bare oneself in public.  This exhibition, in your own words, is not of Shintou's words, but of his identity, his &quot;you&quot;-ness.  Grammatically and rhetorically, in the sentence you actually wrote, Shintou ('you&quot;) is the source of the &quot;intolerance&quot;.  His words are the exhibition of his inward character; his words are, in the sentence you constructed, the exhibition of the intolerance he bears inwardly.<br>
<br>
If you had actually written &quot;Your statements are intolerant&quot;, that would have been one thing.  That would have restricted your comments to Shintou's comments.  You did not, however, actually do so, and your comments, as written, are open to a reasonable person assuming that you meant that Shintou is intolerant--that intolerance is part of Shintou's character.<br>
<br>
Sure, this post is open to the charge that I'm &quot;splitting a hair&quot;, but allow me to point out that claiming you directed your comments at his ideas and not himself is splitting that same hair.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/02 2:44:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=292.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Close readings</span><hr size=1> /yawn <br>
